</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,417,1884]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,1317,1343]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Discussion.</emphasis>
I have examined images of the 
<typeStatus box="[699,797,1318,1344]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carvalho" authorityYear="1987" box="[837,1095,1318,1344]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraensis">
<emphasis box="[837,1095,1318,1344]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Cyrtocapsus paraensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(previously known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[195,293,1354,1380]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">holotype</typeStatus>
male and 
<specimenCount box="[417,545,1354,1380]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="female">two female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[555,664,1354,1380]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">paratypes</typeStatus>
) and compared them with images of the 
<typeStatus box="[1143,1241,1354,1380]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carvalho" authorityYear="1990" box="[1284,1437,1354,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis box="[1284,1437,1354,1380]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">C. bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(known only from the 
<typeStatus box="[420,518,1390,1416]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">holotype</typeStatus>
female and 
<specimenCount box="[668,782,1390,1416]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="female">11 female</specimenCount>
<typeStatus box="[793,902,1390,1416]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">paratypes</typeStatus>
) and conclude, based on the overall size, the distinctive coloration, and fine pubescence, that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carvalho" authorityYear="1990" box="[714,867,1426,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis box="[714,867,1426,1452]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">C. bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carvalho" authorityYear="1987" box="[1105,1250,1426,1452]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraensis">
<emphasis box="[1105,1250,1426,1452]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">C. paraensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In addition, R. Carrenho (pers. comm.) provided additional information on the antennal and leg color of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carvalho" authorityYear="1990" box="[1154,1303,1462,1488]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis box="[1154,1303,1462,1488]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">C. bolivianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was important in helping to interpret infraspecific variation in this species. Although described only three years apart, 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M." box="[151,335,1534,1560]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="445 - 452" refId="ref41963" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. (1990) Mirideos neotropicais, CCCVII: Novas especies da Argentina e Bolivia (Hemiptera). Revista Brasileira de Entomologica, 34, 445 - 452." type="journal article" year="1990">Carvalho (1990)</bibRefCitation>
did not mention the obvious similarities shared by 
<taxonomicName authority="(Carvalho 1987)" baseAuthorityName="Carvalho" baseAuthorityYear="1987" box="[904,1234,1534,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraensis">
<emphasis box="[904,1045,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">C. paraensis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M." box="[1058,1226,1534,1560]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="235 - 239" refId="ref41922" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. (1987) Mirideos neotropicais, CCLXXVIII: Descricoes de duas especies novas de Cyrtocapsus Reuter (Hemiptera). Boletim do Museum Paraense Emilio Goeldi, 3, 235 - 239." type="journal article" year="1987">Carvalho 1987</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Carvalho 1990)" baseAuthorityName="Carvalho" baseAuthorityYear="1990" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Cyrtocapsus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bolivianus">
<emphasis box="[1288,1437,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">C. bolivianus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho, J. C. M." box="[159,330,1570,1596]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="445 - 452" refId="ref41963" refString="Carvalho, J. C. M. (1990) Mirideos neotropicais, CCCVII: Novas especies da Argentina e Bolivia (Hemiptera). Revista Brasileira de Entomologica, 34, 445 - 452." type="journal article" year="1990">Carvalho 1990</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
